Document: ConcavePolygonShape2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_concavepolygonshape2d.rst  
Summary: A 2D polyline shape for physics, used in CollisionPolygon2D's BUILD_SEGMENTS mode as a hollow, configurable shape.  

A 2D polyline shape intended for use in physics, specifically with CollisionPolygon2D when in BUILD_SEGMENTS mode. ConcavePolygonShape2D is a collection of interconnected line segments, allowing creation of polygons of any type or even non-enclosing shapes. However, it remains hollow even if line segments enclose an area, making it unsuitable for physics or detection in many cases.  

Note: When used for collision, ConcavePolygonShape2D works best with static CollisionShape2D nodes like StaticBody2D and may not function well with CharacterBody2D or RigidBody2D in non-static modes.  

Warning: Small physics bodies moving quickly may clip through this shape due to its hollow nature, failing to detect collisions between frames.  

Performance: ConcavePolygonShape2D is the slowest 2D collision shape due to its complexity and should be limited to level geometry. For closed polylines, CollisionPolygon2D's BUILD_SOLIDS mode decomposes the polygon into convex shapes, which can then be used with ConvexPolygonShape2D for better performance.
